Subject: Error in "grep(I)" documentation, or in grep
Index: 	man/man1/grep.1 2.9BSD

Description:
	There is a "-w" switch documented in grep(I) in the manual,
	which is supposed to make the expression search be as if
	surrounded by \< and \>, as in ex.  There is no such flag in grep.

Repeat-By:
	grep -w <any expression>
